This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with the problem of scene labeling, which is a fundamental task in computer vision. The use of contextual information in the proposed framework also aligns with the research focus of cs.CV. 

The paper also involves machine learning techniques, specifically hierarchical models, which suggests that it could also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. 

The use of contextual information and the hierarchical framework also suggests that the paper could belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. 

The paper's focus on optimization of a joint posterior probability suggests that it could also belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category. 

Finally, the paper's use of image patches and applicability to a variety of problems such as object segmentation and edge detection suggests that it could also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
